text: Oskaloosa is an unincorporated community in Barton County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Oskaloosa was established in 1894, and remained in operation until 1953. The community was named after Oskaloosa, Iowa, the native home of a share of the first settlers. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Barton County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Oskaloosa, Missouri
